annotations: Girls just wanna have fun like the Cyndi remake

This is a reference to Cyndi Lauper’s “Girls Just Want To Have Have” cover, which was originally written & recorded by Robert Hazard in 1979. Lyrically, Hazard’s original version is from a male point of view while Lauper’s is from a female point of view.

annotations: You liked to watch the page bleed
Some inks (India ink especially) bleeds through thin papers easily. “Page bleed” is also a printing and design term used to describe the blank margins surround the edge of a printed page

Sat vigil for troubles mourning greens clean
 Still feels damp on the ends of my sleeves
Unfolded, we might read this couplet as depicting her crying for so long that she can wash her vegetables with her tears, soaking her shirt’s cuffs in the process
While “disassembling” means “to take apart,” it’s spelled (and pronounced) similarly to “dissembling,” meaning to lie or deceive. Like many of Zoe’s lyrics, it’s a sort of pun.
